pnp:RoleDefinition.Name: Approve
pnp:RoleDefinition.Description: Can edit and approve pages, list items, and documents.

pnp:RoleDefinition.Name: Manage Hierarchy
pnp:RoleDefinition.Description: Can create sites and edit pages, list items, and documents.

pnp:RoleDefinition.Name: Restricted Read
pnp:RoleDefinition.Description: Can view pages and documents, but cannot view historical versions or user permissions.

pnp:RoleDefinition.Name: Restricted Interfaces for Translation
pnp:RoleDefinition.Description: Can open lists and folders, and use remote interfaces.

Field.Name: ChannelAlias
Field.Description: Pick a word to identify this channel in code, Device Channel panels, previews and other contexts. Warning: If you later change the channel alias, you will have to manually update Master Page mappings, Device Channel panels, and any custom code or markup.

Field.Name: PublishingPageImage
Field.Description: Page Image is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Article Page Content Type as the primary image of the page.

Field.Name: PublishingCacheDisplayName
Field.Description: Display name is used to populate the list of available cache profiles for site owners and page layout owners.

Field.Name: PublishingContactName
Field.Description: Contact Name is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Page Content Type as the name of the person or group who is the contact person for the page.

Field.Name: SummaryLinks2
Field.Description: Summary Links 2 is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Welcome Page Content Type to display a second set of links.

Field.Name: PublishingVaryByCustom
Field.Description: As specified by HttpCachePolicy.SetVaryByCustom in ASP.Net 2.0.

Field.Name: PublishingStartDate
Field.Description: Scheduling Start Date is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used to specify the date and time on which this page will first appear to site visitors.

Field.Name: PublishingVaryByRights
Field.Description: Selecting this check box ensures that users must have identical effective permissions on all securable objects to see the same cached page as any other user.

Field.Name: UserAgentSubstrings
Field.Description: Specify one or more user agent substrings (for example: Windows Phone OS), placing each substring on its own line. When the user agent string of a visiting device contains any of the specified substrings, the channel will force site pages to display using that channel's optimizations, like a different Master Page or Device Channel Panel. You can also trigger this special rendering by using query strings, cookies or custom code, in which case the substrings don't matter.

Field.Name: PublishingIsFurlPage
Field.Description: If checked, the physical URL of this page will not appear in search results. Friendly URLs assigned to this page will always appear.

Field.Name: SeoBrowserTitle
Field.Description: Browser Title is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used as the title that appears at the top of a browser window and may appear in Internet search results.

Field.Name: PublishingPageIcon
Field.Description: Page Icon is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Page Content Type as the icon image for the page.

Field.Name: ChannelDescription
Field.Description: A quick description of the Device Channel

Field.Name: PublishingExpirationDate
Field.Description: Scheduling End Date is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used to specify the date and time on which this page will no longer appear to site visitors.

Field.Name: PublishingCacheAllowWriters
Field.DisplayName: Allow writers to view cached content
Field.Description: Selecting this check box bypasses the normal behavior of not allowing people with edit permissions to have their pages cached. This check box should be selected only in scenarios in which you know that the page will be published, but will not have any content that might be checked out or in draft.

Field.Name: PublishingContactPicture
Field.Description: Contact Picture is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Page Content Type as the picture of the user or group who is the contact person for the page.

Field.Name: PublishingVaryByParam
Field.Description: As specified by HttpCachePolicy.VaryByParams in ASP.Net 2.0.

Field.Name: Audience
Field.Description: Target Audiences is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used to specify audiences to which this page will be targeted.

Field.Name: PublishingCacheEnabled
Field.Description: Selecting this check box turns caching on. If you clear this check box, caching will not take place anywhere this profile is selected. Clearing this check box can be useful for troubleshooting the rendering of all sites and page layouts associated with this cache profile. Remember to select this check box when troubleshooting is complete.

Field.Name: SeoKeywords
Field.Description: Meta Keywords

Field.Name: RedirectURL
Field.Description: Redirect URL is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Redirect Page Content Type as the web address that the page will redirect to.

Field.Name: ChannelPriority
Field.Description: A rank that determines which channel will be assigned to a visitor when the device being used fits into more than one channel

Field.Name: PublishingCacheDisplayDescription
Field.Description: Display description is used to populate the list of available cache profiles for site owners and page layout owners.

Field.Name: PublishingCacheCheckForChanges
Field.Description: Selecting this check box validates on each page request that the site has not changed and flushes the cache on changes to the site. Clearing this check box can improve performance but will not check for updates to the site for the number of seconds specified in duration.

Field.Name: PublishingPageContent
Field.Description: Page Content is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Article Page Content Type as the content of the page.

Field.Name: PublishingContactEmail
Field.Description: Contact E-mail Address is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Page Content Type as the e-mail address of the person or group who is the contact person for the page.

Field.Name: AutomaticUpdate
Field.Description: If this option is selected, the content of this list item will be inserted into web pages as a read-only reference. New versions of this item will automatically appear in the web pages. If the option is not selected, the content of this list item will be inserted into web pages as a copy that page authors can then modify. New versions of this item will not appear in the web pages. Any change to this setting will not affect existing web pages that are using this item.

Field.Name: ShowInRibbon
Field.Description: Select this option if you want this reusable content item to appear in a drop-down menu available during page editing. This will offer authors a quick way to add this item to a page.

Field.Name: PublishingCachePerformACLCheck
Field.Description: Selecting this check box ensures that all items in the cache are appropriately security trimmed. Clearing this check box allows for better performance but should only be applied to sites or page layouts that do not have information that needs security trimming.

Field.Name: ChannelIsActive
Field.Description: Check this box once you've optimized your site for this channel. If you're working on a live site, don't activate this channel before you're done designing it.

Field.Name: PublishingCacheability
Field.Description: As specified by HttpCacheability in ASP.Net 2.0.

Field.Name: PublishingCacheDuration
Field.Description: Duration in seconds to keep the cached version available.

Field.Name: ArticleByLine
Field.Description: Byline is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Article Page Content Type as the byline of the page.

Field.Name: PublishingRollupImage
Field.Description: Rollup Image is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Page Content Type as the image for the page shown in content roll-ups such as the Content By Search web part.

Field.Name: HtmlDesignAssociated
Field.Description: Describes whether a file has a SharePoint master page (.master) or page layout (.aspx) file associated with it. Setting this value to true will re-associate to a previously associated file or create a new file for association.

Field.Name: RobotsNoIndex
Field.Description: Hide from Internet Search Engines is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used to indicate to search engine crawlers that a particular page should not be indexed.

Field.Name: PublishingContact
Field.Description: Contact is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Page Content Type as the person or group who is the contact person for the page.

Field.Name: HtmlDesignPreviewUrl
Field.Description: Edit this field to change the URL of the page you wish to preview.

Field.Name: SeoMetaDescription
Field.Description: Meta Description is a site column created by the Publishing feature. Internet search engines may display this description in search results pages.

Field.Name: PublishingAuthenticatedUse
Field.Description: This check box should be selected for only those policies that you want to allow to be applied to authenticated scenarios by administrators and page layout designers.

Field.Name: PublishingImageCaption
Field.Description: Image Caption is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Article Page Content Type as the caption for the primary image displayed on the page.

Field.Name: ArticleStartDate
Field.Description: Article Date is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Article Page Content Type as the date of the page.

Field.Name: PublishingVaryByHeader
Field.Description: As specified by HttpCachePolicy.VaryByHeaders in ASP.Net 2.0.

Field.Name: SummaryLinks
Field.Description: Summary Links is a site column created by the Publishing feature. It is used on the Welcome Page Content Type to display a set of links.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Search Config Content Type
pnp:ContentType.Description: Designed to facilitate the storage of Search Config information.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Translation Status
pnp:ContentType.Description: Translation State is a Content Type created to represent all the information that is tracked by the Translation Feature.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Html Page Layout
pnp:ContentType.Description: Build a SharePoint page layout - a template for authored page data within a master page - using only HTML. SharePoint will allow you to embed common components and will create and update a functional page layout automatically.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Control Display Template
pnp:ContentType.Description: Control Display Templates control the organization of your results within the web part they are used in and the overall look of the web part. They are used in Content By Search, Search Results, Refinement web parts.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Group Display Template
pnp:ContentType.Description: Group Display Templates are used to group together a number of Item Display Templates. They can appear in Control Display Templates. They are used in Search Results web part.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Item Display Template
pnp:ContentType.Description: Item Display Templates allow you to specify what managed properties are used and how they appear for a result. They are used by Content By Search and Search Results web parts.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Filter Display Template
pnp:ContentType.Description: Filter Display Templates allow you to create customized refinement controls that will appear in Refinement web part.

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_ArticlePage
pnp:ContentType.Description: Created this content type based on "Article Page"

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_News
pnp:ContentType.Description: Use this content type to create the news

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_Scoop
pnp:ContentType.Description: Use this content type to create Scoop News.

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_ExesMsg_OnlyText
pnp:ContentType.Description: Use this content type to create "Only Text " content for Executive Corner web part.

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_ExesMsg_ImageWithText
pnp:ContentType.Description: Use this content type to create "Image or Banner with Text " content for Executive Corner web part.

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_ExesMsg_VideoWithText
pnp:ContentType.Description: Use this content type to create "Video with Text " content for Executive Corner web part.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Catalog-Item Reuse
pnp:ContentType.Description: The Catalog Item Reuse content type is best if you want to create article pages that can be easily reused or republished across your site collections.

pnp:ContentType.Name: Translation Package
pnp:ContentType.Description: Translation Package is a system content type template created by the Translation feature, and it cannot be modified.

pnp:ContentType.Name: KPCU_Happenings
pnp:ContentType.Description: This is Content Type is used in Happenings List

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Content and Structure Reports
pnp:ListInstance.Description: Use the reports list to customize the queries that appear in the Content and Structure Tool views

Field.Description: Type the name of the list template for the CAML list type, or leave blank to search document library template
Field.Name: _x0024_Resources_x003a_cmscore_x1

Field.Description: Type the CAML markup for the report query

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Images
pnp:ListInstance.Description: This system library was created by the Publishing feature to store images that are used on pages in this site.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Pages
pnp:ListInstance.Description: This system library was created by the Publishing feature to store pages that are created in this site.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Reusable Content
pnp:ListInstance.Description: Items in this list contain HTML or text content which can be inserted into web pages. If an item has automatic update selected, the content will be inserted into web pages as a read-only reference, and the content will update if the item is changed. If the item does not have automatic update selected, the content will be inserted as a copy in the web page, and the content will not update if the item is changed.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Site Assets
pnp:ListInstance.Description: Use this library to store files which are included on pages within this site, such as images on Wiki pages.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Site Collection Documents
pnp:ListInstance.Description: This system library was created by the Publishing Resources feature to store documents that are used throughout the site collection.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Site Collection Images
pnp:ListInstance.Description: This system library was created by the Publishing Resources feature to store images that are used throughout the site collection.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Style Library
pnp:ListInstance.Description: Use the style library to store style sheets, such as CSS or XSL files. The style sheets in this gallery can be used by this site or any of its subsites.

pnp:ListInstance.Title: Workflow Tasks
pnp:ListInstance.Description: This system library was created by the Publishing feature to store workflow tasks that are created in this site.
